biggest taboo: the day troops moved into Beijing and dispersed the
massive pro-democracy protest with guns and tanks, killing hundreds
and injuring thousands. Painful memories now lay buried under the
loose gravel of a decade of prosperity and, with public
soul-searching strictly forbidden, the conflicts and trauma they
evoke have been left unresolved. By Elisabeth Rosenthal.
