over violent lyrics that apparently are stock in trade for some of
the bands. In light of Littleton, Colo., and Conyers, they have
reason to be disturbed. If what we suspect is true, we need to do a
bit of adjusting on the First Amendment while we're tinkering with
the Second. Keeping military weapons away from civilians and
keeping guns away from criminals and children has nothing to do
with the right of a militia to bear arms. Marketing violence to
kids has even less to do with freedom of speech and press. (Jim
