Egyptian mummies. The curatorial coup that brought the world-class
mummy collection to the Emory University campus has quietly
resurrected an unsolved mystery over the disappearance, in the
mid-1800s, of the mummified remains of Ramses I, the founder of
ancient Egypt's most powerful pharaoic dynasty. Where did he go? No
one knows. But Emory University scientists say the latest in 20th
Century genetic technology may enable them shed new light on the
riddle if it can answer another question: ``Who's that mummy?''
(Toner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
