<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    KOSOVO'S ETHNIC ALBANIANS CONCENTRATED IN BALKANS REGION
 &HT;    With KOSOVO-REFUGEES-$ADV06.
 &HT;    For Use Sun., June 6 And Thereafter.
 &HT;    By BERT ROUGHTON JR. 
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LEHZE, Albania _ Since NATO began its punishing air campaign
against Serb forces in Yugoslavia on March 24, the U.N. High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) estimates that about 855,000
people, the vast majority of them ethnic Albanians, have left
Kosovo province.
</P>
<P>
   Another 500,000-700,000 -- of Kosovo's 1.8 million ethnic
Albanians -- is believed to be displaced within the embattled Serb
province.
</P>
<P>
   The whereabouts and numbers of the largest concentrations of
refugees, according to UNHCR:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Albania..............................................443,100
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Macedonia.........................................248,400
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Montenegro.........................................68,900
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Bosnia-Herzegovina........................21,700
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Evacuated (from Macedonia)......72,592
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
