thought of as a politician who understands science he began talking
of plans to ``publicly emphasize his faith in God'' and getting
government to work with ``faith-based organizations'' on policy
goals. But Gore, a former divinity student, said at a luncheon last
week that his religious ideals and government service have never
been separate in his mind. (Shepard, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
