</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ Out of the consternation and
confusion over the House report on Chinese spying in the United
States, one fact emerges: Rep. Christopher Cox is not Sen. Joseph
McCarthy, the unprincipled red-baiter of the 1950s. Cox, a
thoughtful California conservative, has made no attempt to exploit
for domestic political gain his committee's findings that China
stole U.S. nuclear secrets. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON. (Filed
Wednesday.)
