most popular herbal remedies now on the market and touted as being
effective at warding off colds, is the subject of an international
symposium this week in KC. The sponsors are the makers of the
stuff, but we'll seek outside experts to sort out the claims made
about the remedy. Ukrainians are there pitching echinacea-laced
vodka and crowing that it's safeguarding those who live near the
Chernobyl nuclear disaster against radiation damage. Echinacea's
boosters admit it can't prevent a cold, but say it might reduce the
symptoms. By ALAN BAVLEY AND WINSTON ROSS. Story will move in the
