<P>
   &QL;  PA Contract Awards States News Service Washington, May 27 --
Northropo Grumman of Pittsburg won a $1.5 million contract from the
Hanscom Air Force Base in Massachusetts for research and
development.
</P>
<P>
   Advanced Construction Services of Pittsburgh won a $296,969
contract from the Postal Service in Columbia, Md., for property
maintenance and repair.
</P>
<P>
   Connaught Laboratories of Swiftwater won a $583,442 contract
from the Dept. of Veterans Affairs in Hines, Ill., for vaccines.
</P>
<P>
   Wyeth Ayerst Laboratories of Philadelphia won a $504,514
contract from the Dept. of Veterans Affairs in Hines, Ill., for flu
virus vaccines.
</P>
<P>
   United Defense LP of York won a $190,066 contract from the Army
in Warren, Mich., for aircraft components.
</P>
<P>
   Litton Systems Inc. of Springfield won a $89,820 contract from
the Navy in Philadelphia for lab equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Narricot Industries Inc. of Philadelphia won a $186,711 contract
from the Defense Personnel Support Center in Philadelphia for
clothing.
</P>
<P>
   National Medical Services Inc. of Willow Grove won a $323,100
contract from the National Institute of Health in Bethesda, Md.,
for research and development.
</P>
<P>
   GRD Inc. of Doyletown won a $613,272 contract from the Dryden
Flight Research Center in Edwards, Calif., for professional support
services.
</P>
<P>
   R&AMP;S Medical Communications Inc. of Gettysburg won a $112,345
contract from the Navy in Washington, D.C., for utilities and
housekeeping services.
</P>
<P>
   United Defense LP of York won a $1 million contract from the
Army in Rock Island, Ill., for weapons.
</P>
<P>
   United Defense LP of York won a $2.3 million contract from the
Army in Warren, Mich., for ground effect vehicles.
</P>
<P>
   SOMAT Co. of Coatsville won a $60,180 contract from the Federal
Prison Camp in Montgomery for a sludge dewatering system.
</P>
