   TRANSPLANT (Seattle) _ Scientists at the University of
Washington and the Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center are
leading a rapidly growing movement to treat autoimmune diseases by
transplantation. The UW is leading a nationwide consortium of
clinical studies aimed at evaluating stem cell replacement for
treatment of a variety of immune disorders such as MS, lupus and
others.
</P>
