that caters to a rock 'n' roll clientele. By Elizabeth Hayt.
Photo. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   GARDEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ Cosmos, a reliable summer bloomer, is
usually available in garden centers. The plants are often part of
the dwarf Sonata series in shades of pink, lilac, rose, white or
mixed. This is unfortunate, because one of the splendid
characteristics of cosmos is the extraordinary height and mass of
bright green, lacy foliage; waxy buds, and broad blooms that a
single tiny seed can produce. The dwarf varieties grow only 20 to
30 inches tall, but the standard varieties reach four feet and
more. By Georgeanne Brennan. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
