r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-RAC-BELMONT-LADN     06-04 0931
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RAC-BELMONT-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BIG TASK AWAITS CHARISMATIC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN MODESTI  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ELMONT, N.Y. _ The Daily Racing Form, in a rare display of
whimsy, printed photographs this week showing the facial
similarities between Charismatic and Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
   Chestnut coats, white stars on foreheads, trickles of white on
sharply tapered noses. The resemblance is uncanny even by equine
standards.
</P>
<P>
   Does it end there? Has Charismatic inherited the Triple Crown
gene from his great-grandsire as well?
</P>
<P>
   Can Charismatic defeat Silverbulletday, the leading filly,
Menifee, the Kentucky Derby and Preakness runner-up, and nine other
3-year-olds in today's Belmont Stakes to end a 21-year Triple Crown
drought, the longest since the 25 years between Citation (1948) and
Secretariat?
</P>
<P>
   And one more question being asked at Belmont Park: Does the
former Santa Anita claiming horse deserve to join Citation,
Secretariat and nine others on the roster of Triple Crown-winning
immortals?
</P>
<P>
   Not even his hairdresser knows for sure.
</P>
<P>
   The easy answer is the one offered Friday morning by Bob
Baffert, who trains Silverbulletday and whose Silver Charm and Real
Quiet lost Triple Crowns in the Belmont the past two years: ``If he
wins, it doesn't matter what anybody thinks.''
</P>
<P>
   The safe answer is that if Charismatic wins _ clinching a $5
million Triple Crown bonus on top of the $600,000 winner's share of
the $1 million Belmont purse for owners Bob and Beverly Lewis _ his
will be the unlikeliest name on the list that begins with Sir
Barton in 1919.
</P>
<P>
   No Triple Crown winner came up through the claiming ranks, the
lowest level of North American racing. But Charismatic ran in
claiming sprints in November and February.
</P>
<P>
   Most Triple Crown winners went into the Kentucky Derby already
considered the leader of the age group; only Assault, who started
the Derby as an 8-1 shot, entered the series at odds higher than
4-1. But Charismatic was 31-1 in the Derby.
</P>
<P>
   Most Triple Crown winners dominated the Derby and Preakness;
none of them won the Derby by less than 1{ lengths, and only four
won the Preakness by less than 1{. But Charismatic and jockey Chris
Antley won the Derby by a diminishing neck and the Preakness by a
shrinking 1{.
</P>
<P>
   Does any of that lead to the hard judgment that Charismatic
doesn't deserve a Triple Crown?
</P>
<P>
   Hey, somebody has to be the worst on the list.
</P>
<P>
   But since he finished fourth in the April Santa Anita Derby as a
44-1 laughingstock, Charismatic has turned into a horse good enough
to beat this season's uninspiring group of 3-year-old colts and
geldings in the 1 1/16-mile Lexington Stakes, 1\-mile Derby and 1
3/16-mile Preakness.
</P>
<P>
   ``Don't discredit the horse because I misjudged him,'' said
trainer D. Wayne Lukas, referring to the decision to twice risk him
for $62,500 claiming prices.
</P>
<P>
   Lukas calls his horsemanship since _ recognizing Charismatic's
affinity for hard workouts and frequent racing _ the best training
job of his Hall of Fame career.
</P>
<P>
   And Lukas hasn't let up on Charismatic during the Triple Crown
series. He said the horse has dropped about 75 pounds, to an
estimated 1,200 pounds, which is still big for his average frame.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's a little racier now,'' Lukas said.
</P>
<P>
   Lukas classifies the son of Summer Squall as
``low-maintenance,'' saying he has been given two Lasix
(anti-bleeding) and two phynylbutazone (anti-inflammatory)
injections since the Kentucky Derby.
</P>
<P>
   So Lukas said he's confident Charismatic is in good shape for
the Belmont.
</P>
<P>
   But the colt, likely to be favored today for the first time
since his maiden victory 11 races back, will have to prove himself
against several obstacles.
</P>
<P>
   _The distance. A mile and a half is one-quarter mile longer than
he or any opponent has raced or is likely to race again. It has
been the undoing of many Derby-Preakness winners.
</P>
<P>
   Of the 14 horses who lost a Triple Crown in the Belmont, 11 were
running ahead of the eventual spoiler at one point in the race.
</P>
<P>
   _The filly. He has never faced her because she has never faced
males before. And Silverbulletday's talent _ eight straight
victories against other fillies _ and the chance she and jockey
Jerry Bailey can set a slow pace today make her hard for most
handicappers to dismiss.
</P>
<P>
   ``The pace will be determined by others in the race,'' said
Antley, who is trying to cap a sensational comeback from weight
problems. ``When the gates open, it's a whole new ballgame.''
</P>
<P>
   Silverbulletday would be the third filly _ the first since Tanya
in 1905 _ to win the Belmont. She's the first to challenge a Triple
Crown hopeful.
</P>
<P>
   _Menifee. He's the obvious ``spoiler'' based on his close
finishes at Churchill Downs and Pimlico. Trainer Elliott Walden was
in the same position last year and got the Belmont upset with
Victory Gallop.
</P>
<P>
   ``Menifee is probably showing less signs of stress, and he's
probably coming up to the race a little better (than Victory Gallop
did),'' Walden said this week.
</P>
<P>
   Other logical spoilers are Best of Luck, the Peter Pan Stakes
winner trained by ``Giant Killer'' Allen Jerkens, and Derby Trial
winner Patience Game, whose pedigree and light campaign give him a
chance to improve.
</P>
<P>
   Before Charismatic's Lexington Stakes victory, Lukas told the
Lewises their colt is ``definitely a Belmont horse.'' Back then,
Lukas couldn't have been thinking he's a Triple Crown horse.
</P>
<P>
   Is he?
</P>
<P>
   Somewhere above Belmont Park, great-granddad will be watching,
waiting to find out.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
