<P>
   ENVIRONMENTAL-LAWSUITS (Roebuck, S.C.) _ A quarter century after
Congress gave citizens broad powers to enforce environmental laws
through private suits, judges across the country are cutting back
so sharply on those suits that environmental groups have lost much
of their power in court, legal experts on both sides of the issue
say. The trend, some legal experts say, represents one of the least
noted but most profound setbacks for the environmental movement in
decades. By William Glaberson.
</P>
<P>
